<br>
I was at the TTC platform this morning waiting for a bus, and there was a bird on the ground. It looked to be in a lot of pain. I stood before it, it was obviously still breathing, breathing very heavily, but in a lot of pain. Not knowing what to do, I told one of the attendants that was working about it. He didn't care. <br>
<br>
So I got on my bus and sat at the window, looking down at the bird. Still breathing, it's beak opening and closing, it's still laying on its side. And then, it just kind of stopped. The birds beak just suddenly stopped and a breeze swept over its body, rustling its feathers. Nature had done it's course and the bird passed on, it's soul flew away on the wind. Or so I prayed to the earthmother. <br>
<br>
That was the first time I've ever witnessed death.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=larraquemeleagrance>Larraque Meleagrance</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Radical Dreamer</span><br>  Posts: 1830<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/29/03 8:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3771.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I watched a sparrow die this morning...</span><hr size=1> There is no real point to this. I just felt I needed to put it into words and express myself.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kuladen>kuladen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I was a mod<br>for an hour<br>and all I got<br>
